Losses at the Bundeswehr: Machine guns disappear without a trace
Friday, 27. September 2019
Six MG3 machine guns have still disappeared.
In recent years, the Bundeswehr has lost numerous weapons and tens of thousands of rounds of ammunition, including three machine guns. In most cases, the whereabouts are unclear; the opposition speaks of a "frightening" extent.
With the Bundeswehr, weapons and ammunition disappear again and again – many of them without a trace. Since the beginning of 2014, the troops have recorded the loss of 39 weapons, 39 weapon parts and almost 20,000 rounds of ammunition, according to a list classified as classified by the Federal Ministry of Defence, on which the German editorial network reports.
According to the paper from the office of State Secretary for Defence Peter Tauber of the CDU, two weapons, one part of them and 3,474 rounds of ammunition have reappeared to date. In addition, six machine guns of the type MG3, eleven rifles of the type G3, four rifles of the type G36, six signal pistols and two pistols of the type P8 are still missing. Furthermore, 30 weapon barrels for machine guns of the type MG3 are missing.
The extent of the loss of weapons and ammunition in the Bundeswehr is "frightening", said the left-wing Martina Renner, member of the Bundestag. This is all the more true because hardly anything has been found in the course of investigations, and the left-wing politician Renner spoke of a "poor record." Renner criticised the fact that the list does not indicate whether the missing ammunition is the one found in connection with the investigations against the suspected terrorist Bundeswehr officer Franco A. "And this even though a supporter of Franco A. was recently convicted of possessing these ammunition," said Renner.
