According to official figures, the time of the earthquake is 1: 59 p.m. (local time), and only a few minutes after the first earthquake, according to CNN Turkey, there was an aftershock, which was reported to have a magnitude of 4.0 on the Richter scale.
Only on Tuesday an earthquake of the strength 4.6 had shook the Turkish Marmara region - it was to be felt to Istanbul. Also its epicenter had lain in the Marmara sea west of the million-metropolis, communicated the disaster protection authority Afad already on Tuesday.
