We will continue to buy our natural gas from there, "said Erdogan in New York, where he attended the UN General Assembly.
Erdogan admitted, however, that Turkey had problems with the import of Iranian oil, as some companies had "withdrawn because of the US threats".
Nevertheless, Turkey will "continue our relations with Iran, especially on this issue and on many other issues," said the Turkish president, who has repeatedly criticized the US sanctions against Iran in the past.
Since its withdrawal from the international nuclear agreement with Iran, the US has pursued a policy of "maximum pressure" on the Islamic Republic. According to the US, Iran is secretly pursuing a nuclear program and is not complying with the agreement.
Their sanctions have led to the collapse of Iranian oil exports and a severe economic crisis in Iran. Tensions in the Gulf region have intensified considerably in recent months.
U.S. government wants to restrict reception of refugees
The US Department of State said Thursday that the annual ceiling of a resettlement program would be lowered from the current 30,000 to 18,000 refugees, a 40% cut.
The State Department said that while the U.S. remains committed to supporting refugees, the most important task is to protect and serve U.S. citizens, and that the U.S. immigration system is currently overloaded.
The U.S. government intends to concentrate in the future on the reception of two refugee groups: People who are persecuted because of their faith - and Iraqis who have helped the U.S. military in the country and are thus in danger, as the statement of the State Department shows. From Honduras, Guatemala and El Salvador, on the other hand, a maximum of 1500 refugees are to be taken in.
Launched in 1980, the program selects refugees from UN camps around the world and resettles them in the U.S. The ceiling of 18,000 refugees for the 2020 budget year would be the lowest in the program ’ s history. Even the current ceiling of 30,000 is a low one. When US President Donald Trump ’ s predecessor, Barack Obama, left the White House, the number was just under 85,000.
"This is a very sad day for America," said the head of the International Rescue Committee, David Miliband. "The US will continue to damage its leadership role in protecting the world's most vulnerable people," he said.
Trump is trying to strictly limit immigration to the US, legally and illegally, and the US government says it expects to receive 350,000 asylum applications in the coming fiscal year. These numbers are separate from the resettlement program.
Donald Trump - "Close to a Spy"
US President Donald Trump has accused whistleblowers of espionage in the whistleblower ’ s affair. Whoever accuses the whistleblower of abuse of power of providing evidence, "comes close to being an informer," Trump said in a recording of a private event on Thursday in New York, according to several US media reports.
According to this, Trump was speaking in front of employees of the American UN Mission. When asked about the person who informed the whistleblower about controversial events in the White House, he replied, “It ’ s close to a spy. ” Then Trump added,“ Do you know what we did in the old days when we were smart? Right. The spies and betrayals, we used to handle it a bit differently than we do now. ”
The Democrats strongly criticized Trump ’ s statements, accusing him of intimidating witnesses. It was also an attempt to obstruct a congressional investigation into a possible impeachment case against him, wrote the chairs of the House of Representatives ’ foreign affairs, intelligence, and oversight committees.
The whistleblower accuses the president of having abused his office in a recently published complaint in order to ask another country to interfere in the US election of 2020. Specifically, it concerns, among other things, his controversial phone conversation with his Ukrainian counterpart Volodymyr Zelensky in the summer: In the conversation, Trump suggested to him to investigate his possible Democratic challenger Joe Biden and his son Hunter in Ukraine. Trump denies any wrongdoing.
It is still unclear who the whistleblower himself and his informants are. However, as the New York Times reports, the whistleblower is said to be an analyst of the CIA foreign intelligence service.
Refugee boat capsized: Baby and toddlers drown in Aegean Sea
Again and again people try to cross the Aegean Sea from Turkey to Greece. Regularly capsize the often far too small boats. At the sinking of a rubber dinghy seven migrants have now died - including five children.
Seven migrants died in the sinking of a rubber dinghy off the Greek island of Chios. According to the Greek coast guard, one of the victims was a baby and four other children. Accordingly, four children, three women and five men were rescued from the floods by the crew of a passing ferry.
According to the local news portal of Chios, Alithia.gr., the migrants had left Turkey in the morning trying to reach the small archipelago of Inousses in the northeast of the island of Chios. Inousses is located between Chios and the Turkish mainland.
It is not yet known which states the migrants come from. Currently, hundreds of migrants from Turkey are crossing over to the Greek islands in the east of the Aegean Sea, mostly in boats that are much too small. Last year, according to the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), 174 people were killed on this route.
