At the end of an international week of climate strike, the Fridays for Future movement is once again planning actions and rallies in dozens of countries around the world. New Zealand and Australia are likely to make the start before the protests move across Europe to North America, where climate activist Greta Thunberg wanted to take part in a mass rally in Montreal, Canada. Demonstrators also wanted to rally in front of the White House in Washington.
